;Task:
Show the &nbsp; [[wp:Stooge sort|Stooge Sort]] &nbsp; for an array of integers. 


The Stooge Sort algorithm is as follows:
 <b>algorithm</b> stoogesort(<b>array</b> L, i = 0, j = <b>length</b>(L)-1)
      <b>if</b> L[j] < L[i] <b>then</b>
          L[i] <b>â†”</b> L[j]
      <b>if</b> j - i > 1 <b>then</b>
          t <b>:=</b> (j - i + 1)/3
          stoogesort(L, i  , j-t)
          stoogesort(L, i+t, j  )
          stoogesort(L, i  , j-t)
      <b>return</b> L
<br><br>


=={{header|JavaScript}}==
<lang javascript>function stoogeSort (array, i, j) {
    if (j === undefined) {
        j = array.length - 1;
    }

    if (i === undefined) {
        i = 0;
    }

    if (array[j] < array[i]) {
        var aux = array[i];
        array[i] = array[j];
        array[j] = aux;
    }

    if (j - i > 1) {
        var t = Math.floor((j - i + 1) / 3);
        stoogeSort(array, i, j-t);
        stoogeSort(array, i+t, j);
        stoogeSort(array, i, j-t);
    }
};</lang>
Example:
<lang javascript>arr = [9,1,3,10,13,4,2];
stoogeSort(arr);
console.log(arr);</lang>
{{out}}
<pre>[1, 2, 3, 4, 9, 10, 13]</pre>
